## tool-llm-delegation: llm_call, llm_timeout, and stream tool definitions

### llm_call(action: str, model_key: str = "", value: bool = None) → str
Manage the tool_call_available flag for LLM models.
- action="list" — show all models with their tool_call_available status. Always allowed.
- action="set"  — enable or disable delegation for a specific model, or all models if model_key is omitted.

### llm_timeout(action: str, model_key: str = "", seconds: int = None) → str
Manage llm_call_timeout for LLM delegation.
- action="list" — show current timeouts for all models. Always allowed.
- action="set"  — update the timeout in seconds. Omit model_key to set all models.

### stream(action: str, value: bool = None) → str
Control agent_call streaming for the current session.
- action="get" — show current streaming setting.
- action="set" — enable or disable real-time token relay (value=true/false).
Always allowed — no gate required.
